      "id": 69668,
      "name": "dmjones",
      "username": "dmjones",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/dmjones/{size}/7902_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-01-29T20:33:03.849Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I use HR ERG mode to do a 45 minute zone 2 ride. However, I\u2019m often nearly 15 minutes into my ride before I reach my target BPM.</p>\n<p>I saw <a href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/t/solved-hr-control-mode-does-not-work-how-i-expect-it-to/45530\">this topic</a>, which explains I can create my own custom ramp-up phase before switching to HR ERG mode. However, it would be more convenient if there was some ability to customise the aggression of HR ERG mode.</p>\n<p>Ideally, I\u2019d like to hit my target BPM in 5 minutes or so. I\u2019d love to see a new setting we can tweak, to add a scaling factor to how quickly the power increases.</p>\n<p>In a truly perfect world, I\u2019d love some way to say \u201c<em>Get me to the target BPM in X minutes</em>\u201d when planning the training session.</p>",
